  "text": "The SPPB is based on a timed short distance walk (4 m), repeated chair stands and balance test. This test is reliable [CITATION_1] and valid for predicting institutionalization, hospital admission, mortality and disability [36e39]. Each task is scored by the research coordinator from 0 to 4, with 4 indicating best level of performance and 0 the inability to complete the test. A summary score (0e12) is then calculated.",
